- 'Roles blooming with more than one employee' refers to job titles with more than one employee;
- 'Sown the seeds of a Retirement Plan' means the employees have a 'Retirement Plan' benefit;
- 'Received their due rewards' means the employees have a payroll status of 'paid';
- 'Joined us during the spring of 2020 to the winter of 2022' refers to the join dates between January 1, 2020, and December 31, 2022.

- "blossomed like flowers" metaphorically refers to employees who have shown significant growth or improvement;
- "shining with an average performance rating above 3" indicates employees who have performed well, as a rating above 3 is considered good;
- "since 2021" specifies the time frame for the performance evaluations.

- 'Health-insured' refers to employees who have the 'Health Insurance' benefit;
- 'Well-performing' refers to employees with a performance rating of 3 or higher;
- 'Since the new year began' refers to the period starting from January 1, 2021.

- "shining stars" refers to the top-performing employees;
- "earned the highest accolades" refers to having the highest average performance rating;
- "most training under their belt" refers to having completed the most training sessions.

- A "main caretaker of their role" refers to an employee whose role is marked as primary (`is_primary = 1`);
- "Not extending their care to dependents" means the employee is not receiving benefits for dependents (`is_dependent = 0`);
- The "departments" are represented by `block_name` in the `blocks` table.

